      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * David Broughton</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:170px;\"><a href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/html/chess_computers_-_the_uk_story.html\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/9/90/David_Broughton_1_70_x_70.JPG\" width=\"168\" height=\"210\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:David_Broughton_1_70_x_70.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>David Broughton <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>David C. Broughton</b>, (died on February 02, 2017)<br />\nwas a British computer consultant and computer chess programmer. His first chess program <a href=\"/Vega\" title=\"Vega\">Vega</a>, written on the <a href=\"/Z80\" title=\"Z80\">Z80</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NorthStar_Horizon\">North Star Horizon</a> machine, had finished 2nd behind <a href=\"/Sargon\" title=\"Sargon\">Sargon</a> at the <a href=\"/PCW-MCC_1979\" title=\"PCW-MCC 1979\">2nd PCW-MCC</a> tournament held in London in November 1979, and he was soon recruited by <a href=\"/David_Levy\" title=\"David Levy\">David Levy</a> and <a href=\"/Kevin_O%E2%80%99Connell\" title=\"Kevin O’Connell\">Kevin O’Connell</a> to work for their companies <a href=\"/Philidor_Software\" title=\"Philidor Software\">Philidor Software</a> and since 1981 <a href=\"/Intelligent_Software\" title=\"Intelligent Software\">Intelligent Software</a>. He worked on the project <a href=\"/Philidor\" title=\"Philidor\">Philidor</a> which <a href=\"/8086\" title=\"8086\">8086</a> port emerged to <a href=\"/Parker_Chess\" title=\"Parker Chess\">Parker Chess</a>, and to the <a href=\"/Saitek\" title=\"Saitek\">SciSys</a> <a href=\"/Chess_Champion_Mark_V\" title=\"Chess Champion Mark V\">Chess Champion Mark V</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. Broughton’s work for the Mark V was in the form of Z80 <a href=\"/Assembly\" title=\"Assembly\">assembly</a>. As the Mark V had a <a href=\"/6502\" title=\"6502\">6502</a> processor, the program had to be extensively translated and rewritten. So credit for the Mark V program has to go both to <a href=\"/Mark_Taylor\" title=\"Mark Taylor\">Mark Taylor</a> and David Broughton, though David Levy is known to credit the Mark V to Taylor <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. David Broughton died on February 02, 2017. His wife Dina died more recently on March 10, 2019 <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=David_Broughton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/David_Levy\" title=\"David Levy\">David Levy</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">David Broughton</a>, <a href=\"/Mark_Taylor\" title=\"Mark Taylor\">Mark Taylor</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i>The SEX Algorithm in Computer Chess</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#12_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 12, No. 1</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/SEX_Algorithm\" title=\"SEX Algorithm\">SEX Algorithm</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=David_Broughton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.schachcomputer.info/forum/showthread.php?t=5925\">David Broughton Turnier</a> by <a href=\"/Thorsten_Czub\" title=\"Thorsten Czub\">Thorsten Czub</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Schachcomputer.info</a>, May 01, 2019</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.hiarcs.net/forums/viewtopic.php?t=9941\">Philidor/Parker Chess for PC (1983)</a> by Ben Redic Fy Fazan, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">HIARCS Forum</a>, March 29, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.hiarcs.net/forums/viewtopic.php?t=10011\">David Broughton is dead</a> by <a href=\"/Fernando_Villegas\" title=\"Fernando Villegas\">Fernando</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">HIARCS Forum</a>, June 04, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.schachcomputer.info/forum/showthread.php?t=6209\">David Broughtons Philidor DOS Schachprogramm</a> by <a href=\"/Thorsten_Czub\" title=\"Thorsten Czub\">mclane</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Schachcomputer.info Community</a>, June 09, 2020</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://prodeo.actieforum.com/t256-david-broughtons-computer-chess-engine-philidor-mkv-mk-vi\">David Broughtons computer chess Engine Philidor / MKV / MK VI</a> by <a href=\"/Thorsten_Czub\" title=\"Thorsten Czub\">Mclane</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">ProDeo Forum</a>, February 12, 2021</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=David_Broughton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=430\">David Broughton's ICGA Tournaments</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/html/chess_computers_-_the_uk_story.html\">Chess Computers - The UK Story</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/index.html\">Chess Computer UK</a> by <a href=\"/Mike_Watters\" title=\"Mike Watters\">Mike Watters</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.schach-computer.info/wiki/index.php/Broughton,_David\">Broughton, David</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.schach-computer.info/wiki/index.php/Hauptseite_En\">Schachcomputer.info Wiki</a> (Interview with David Broughton, February 2006 by 'hard)</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.iwpcug.org/davidbro/\">David Broughton's Puzzles &amp; Programs</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=David_Broughton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/html/chess_computers_-_the_uk_story.html\">Chess Computers - The UK Story</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/index.html\">Chess Computer UK</a> by <a href=\"/Mike_Watters\" title=\"Mike Watters\">Mike Watters</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/html/chess_champion_mark_v.html\">Chess Champion Mark V</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/index.html\">Chess Computer UK</a> by <a href=\"/Mike_Watters\" title=\"Mike Watters\">Mike Watters</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/html/chess_computers_-_the_uk_story.html\">Chess Computers - The UK Story</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesscomputeruk.com/index.html\">Chess Computer UK</a> by <a href=\"/Mike_Watters\" title=\"Mike Watters\">Mike Watters</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.schachcomputer.info/forum